com.wx.fx.gui.window

Interface StageInfo

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleStageInfo

    public interface StageInfo
    This interface provides all the basic information needed to build a specific a Stage (window).

    Created on 18/07/2015

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default java.util.ResourceBundle getBundleBase()
      Defines the name of the ResourceBundle to be loaded with this stage (or null if no bundle should be associated).
      boolean isModal()
      Defines if this stage is modal or not.
      java.lang.String location()
      Defines the location of the corresponding FXML file.
      default int stageGroup()
      Defines this stage group that defines this stage behaviour in relation with other stages.

    • Method Detail

      • isModal

        boolean isModal()
        Defines if this stage is modal or not. For more information on modality, see Modality
        Returns:
        true if this stage is modal

      • location

        java.lang.String location()
        Defines the location of the corresponding FXML file.

        e.g: /com/wx/fx/transfer/TransferDialog.fxml

        Returns:
        The location of this stage FXML file.

      • getBundleBase

        default java.util.ResourceBundle getBundleBase()
        Defines the name of the ResourceBundle to be loaded with this stage (or null if no bundle should be associated).
        Returns:
        The name of this stage's bundle or null if no bundle should be used

      • stageGroup

        default int stageGroup()
        Defines this stage group that defines this stage behaviour in relation with other stages. For more information on stage groups, see StageManager.
        Returns:
        This stage's group
